  "dataFlow": "A build request enters via POST /api/build (authenticated by HMAC session cookie) or is auto-created by the autonomy poller reading Linear tickets. The FastAPI backend calls create_session() which allocates a BuildSession in the in-memory _sessions dict and atomically persists it to disk. run_build() is dispatched as an asyncio task. Phase 1 (clone): git clone of the target repo into app/workspaces/{sid}/. Phase 2 (plan): if plan_discovery is set, the TAO orchestrator calls the planner agent via claude_agent_sdk to decompose the brief into TaskSpecs; otherwise the brief passes directly. Phase 3 (generate): _run_claude_via_sdk() spawns a ClaudeSDKClient with bypassPermissions, streams AssistantMessage and ToolUse events to session.output_lines, and commits changes inside the workspace. Phase 4 (evaluate): _run_single_eval() invokes a second ClaudeSDKClient with the git diff and original brief, parses a structured score (COMPLETENESS/CORRECTNESS/CONCISENESS/FORMAT/OVERALL), and appends low-scoring lessons to .harness/lessons.jsonl. Phase 5 (test/ship): run_ship_phase() applies the hard quality gate and, on pass, pushes the workspace commits via git push. All phase state changes are persisted atomically (write-to-tmp → os.replace). output_lines are streamed in real-time to connected WebSocket clients (/ws/build/{sid}) and SSE consumers (/api/sessions/{sid}/logs). Supabase receives fire-and-forget event rows via supabase_log.py for gate_checks and alert_escalations. The MCP server (mcp/pi-ceo-server.js) reads the same .harness/ directory over stdio JSON-RPC 2.0 and exposes it to Claude Desktop. Inbound Telegram messages arrive either via webhook at POST /webhook/telegram (Railway) or via polling in scripts/marathon_telegram_inbox.py (Cowork), are written as JSON to .harness/telegram-inbox/, and are drained/classified by scripts/marathon_watchdog.py every 30 minutes. Pi-SEO scan results flow: cron trigger → cron.py dispatch → scanner.py scans each project repo → writes .harness/scan-results/{project}/{date}-{type}.json → triage.py creates Linear tickets → pi_seo_monitor.py computes deltas and writes .harness/monitor-digests/{timestamp}.json.",
